F15 Strike Eagle


The McDonnell Douglas (now Boeing) F-15E Strike Eagle is an American all-weather multirole strike fighter[6] derived from the McDonnell Douglas F-15 Eagle. The F-15E was designed in the 1980s for long-range, high-speed interdiction without relying on escort or electronic-warfare aircraft


First Flight: 1986

Engine Type :Twin Engine

Range :5700 KM

Weight :20410 Kg

Speed :3050 KM/hr
